12:02.315 --> 12:04.322
I can't believe I'm leaving in three weeks.

12:04.367 --> 12:06.053
Ugh. I wanna spend every minute

12:06.073 --> 12:07.715
of these next three weeks with you.

12:07.785 --> 12:10.283
No family, no friends. Just us,

12:10.403 --> 12:12.761
in a box, staring at each other.

12:12.881 --> 12:14.327
(Chuckles) I thought
you were the smart one.

12:14.362 --> 12:16.600
Summer's three months, not three weeks.

12:16.720 --> 12:18.917
No, I know, but I told you...

12:19.102 --> 12:21.645
I got accepted to that
summer program at Vassar.

12:21.956 --> 12:24.028
Yeah, but I didn't think
that was during the summer.

12:24.033 --> 12:26.286
Well, when did you think it was?

12:26.406 --> 12:28.198
I don't know. I thought it was...

12:28.318 --> 12:30.155
a course where you study summer.

12:30.150 --> 12:31.962
I mean, I remember, 'cause I thought,

12:31.992 --> 12:34.069
"man, Vassar sounds pretty easy."

12:34.707 --> 12:36.062
(Sighs)

12:36.182 --> 12:37.023
What about this?

12:37.093 --> 12:38.810
I don't know. You're on your own.

12:38.860 --> 12:40.571
Buy it, don't buy it. I don't care.

12:40.586 --> 12:41.647
I told you I'm out.

12:41.717 --> 12:42.849
Come on, dad.

12:42.924 --> 12:44.749
We both know you're not out.

12:44.783 --> 12:46.102
I'm just a kid.

12:46.172 --> 12:48.334
Am I really gonna take
the fall for a bad present?

12:48.454 --> 12:49.587
I don't think so.

12:50.036 --> 12:52.729
I can pick it, but if
I pick something lame,

12:53.192 --> 12:54.926
this thing's gonna be on you.

12:56.528 --> 12:57.864
Damn it.

12:58.745 --> 12:59.926
(Grumbles)

13:00.046 --> 13:01.299
(Cash register beeping)

13:01.333 --> 13:03.235
Hey. How about these?

13:03.402 --> 13:04.326
Pants?

13:04.371 --> 13:05.797
Yeah. She likes pants.

13:05.917 --> 13:07.044
She's always wearing 'em.

13:07.279 --> 13:08.673
That's true.

13:09.081 --> 13:10.375
And look, they come in yellow.

13:11.012 --> 13:13.510
<i>Hey, I don't think she
has any yellow pants.</i>

13:13.745 --> 13:14.876
You ever seen her in yellow pants?

13:14.926 --> 13:15.777
I haven't.

13:15.962 --> 13:18.134
And check it out. They're on sale.

13:18.209 --> 13:21.212
No way. Why would these
awesome yellow pants be on sale?

13:21.237 --> 13:22.599
This is good. She's always saying

13:22.599 --> 13:23.681
she wants something personal.

13:23.801 --> 13:25.442
How much more personal
can you get than pants?

13:25.713 --> 13:27.594
- Yeah.
- She'll never see it coming.

13:27.995 --> 13:29.216
Nailed it.

13:31.107 --> 13:32.184
Excuse me, ma'am?

13:32.794 --> 13:34.862
I'm trying to buy pants for my wife.

13:34.982 --> 13:36.168
You're close to her size.

13:36.168 --> 13:39.096
If you were a little less
wide, what size would you be?

13:42.209 --> 13:42.925
Hmm.

13:44.006 --> 13:44.922
I can't believe this.

13:44.927 --> 13:46.589
I had really big plans for us this summer.

13:46.896 --> 13:47.700
You did?

13:47.745 --> 13:50.088
Yeah. Like, well, we were gonna...

13:50.208 --> 13:51.239
go to the mall,

13:51.469 --> 13:52.811
drive around, and...

13:53.021 --> 13:53.797
go tubing.

13:53.837 --> 13:55.168
And you're just gonna throw all that away

13:55.205 --> 13:56.705
to study art with some old dude.

13:56.739 --> 13:57.840
Axl, come on.

13:57.874 --> 14:00.142
You know how much I wanna
be with you this summer.

14:00.176 --> 14:03.197
But I can't blow a chance
like this just to go tubing.

14:03.238 --> 14:05.161
(Scoffs) "Just" to go tubing?

14:05.159 --> 14:08.283
Uh, do you even understand tubing, hmm?

14:08.318 --> 14:11.331
You go down a river...
in tubes. It is awesome.

14:11.366 --> 14:14.005
We have a separate tube
just for a cooler, you know?

14:14.010 --> 14:15.611
At some point, we all link arms,

14:15.602 --> 14:17.626
- make a big wall of tubes.
- Look.

14:18.280 --> 14:20.257
This is a huge opportunity for me.

14:20.297 --> 14:22.093
But this... this is a huge tube-a-tunity.

14:23.074 --> 14:25.528
Sorry. I don't know what to say.

14:25.573 --> 14:27.720
It totally sucks, but

14:28.140 --> 14:30.137
come on. I mean, you know,

14:30.633 --> 14:32.680
it's not like we're
gonna be together anyway.

14:33.286 --> 14:34.710
<i>*</i>

14:35.368 --> 14:37.325
Whoa. What does... what does that mean?

14:38.317 --> 14:39.754
I don't know. I mean,

14:39.874 --> 14:41.816
we're gonna be in separate states...

14:42.006 --> 14:44.219
a thousand miles away from each other.

14:44.844 --> 14:46.546
We were gonna be having this conversation

14:46.546 --> 14:47.993
in three months anyway, right?

14:48.478 --> 14:50.470
We're just having it now instead.

14:50.520 --> 14:51.251
I mean,

14:51.857 --> 14:53.524
what did you think was gonna happen?

14:54.635 --> 14:56.332
I think you know me well enough to know

14:56.347 --> 14:57.703
that I don't think.

15:00.251 --> 15:03.139
But we still have the next three weeks.

15:03.519 --> 15:05.776
- Can't we just focus on that and have fun?
- (Song ends, microphone feedback whines)

15:05.786 --> 15:07.833
(Sean, amplified voice) Hey,
everybody, I'm Sean donahue,

15:07.868 --> 15:10.936
- president of the class of 2013...
- Well, why wait three weeks not to be together?

15:11.141 --> 15:13.829
If we're not gonna be together,
let's not be together now.

15:14.180 --> 15:15.346
(Drumroll)

15:15.421 --> 15:17.844
And the prom king is... (Inhales deeply)

15:17.889 --> 15:20.297
Yes! My boy Axl Heck.

15:20.322 --> 15:21.283
(Cymbal crashes)

15:21.403 --> 15:23.650
(Cheering)

15:24.625 --> 15:26.923
(Whistles)

15:31.297 --> 15:33.684
All right. And the prom
queen is... (Drumroll)

15:33.729 --> 15:35.139
I think we all saw this one coming...

15:35.136 --> 15:37.054
(Hey ocean!) * I'm looking out the window *

15:37.054 --> 15:39.977
♪ of this big, big ship ♪

15:39.961 --> 15:42.899
♪ and it's really coming down outside ♪

15:42.914 --> 15:45.422
And now the king and queen
will dance with their dates.

15:46.348 --> 15:48.572
♪ And something in her eyes ♪

15:48.606 --> 15:51.523
♪ is like the morning mist ♪

15:51.542 --> 15:56.980
♪ as it lifts to show
the world's still alive ♪

15:57.014 --> 15:59.292
♪

15:59.307 --> 16:02.751
♪ somebody once told me ♪

16:02.921 --> 16:04.773
♪

16:05.323 --> 16:07.902
♪ you're gonna know right away ♪

16:08.226 --> 16:10.139
♪

16:10.179 --> 16:11.400
(Whispers) It's destiny.

16:11.435 --> 16:15.675
♪ Once you find that secret somebody ♪

16:16.200 --> 16:21.296
♪ to hold for the rest of your days ♪

16:28.723 --> 16:30.505
♪ You think it might be fierce ♪

16:30.520 --> 16:32.722
♪ to get your lip or eyebrow pierced ♪

16:32.777 --> 16:34.599
♪ but that process isn't very clean ♪

16:34.619 --> 16:36.425
♪ it can get infected, mm-hmm ♪

16:36.816 --> 16:40.840
♪ a temporary tattoo
is a fun way to rebel ♪

16:40.880 --> 16:42.762
♪ and good old-fashioned brooding ♪

16:42.767 --> 16:44.889
♪ gets the job done just as well ♪

16:44.944 --> 16:48.010
♪ so think before you ink ♪

16:48.130 --> 16:49.994
♪

16:50.024 --> 16:51.170
Don't deface your body

16:51.165 --> 16:52.697
just to get back at your parents.

16:52.732 --> 16:54.635
- That ain't cool.
- (Strums chord)

16:56.196 --> 16:58.313
So, let's rap.

16:58.484 --> 17:01.928
Parents and teens don't always
see eye to eye, now do they?

17:02.048 --> 17:02.869
No way.

17:02.884 --> 17:04.471
I'm usually so close with my mom,

17:04.476 --> 17:06.387
but ever since I got my driver's license,

17:06.407 --> 17:08.896
she's like, "drive here. Drive there.

17:09.017 --> 17:10.742
Pick up your dance belt at the store."

17:10.777 --> 17:12.990
I know. It's like a license
gives you all this freedom,

17:13.055 --> 17:14.675
but in some ways, you're
kind of a prisoner.

17:14.705 --> 17:16.417
And now they got me driving grammy bottig

17:16.433 --> 17:17.268
- around on the weekends.
- (Sighs heavily)

17:17.292 --> 17:19.273
I am sorry, but I have better things to do

17:19.266 --> 17:21.233
than watching her pay for a cinnamon bun

17:21.229 --> 17:22.844
with a giant jar of pennies.

17:22.964 --> 17:25.902
Oh! Wah, wah, wah!

17:26.107 --> 17:27.964
Poor you guys!

17:28.085 --> 17:31.023
You know, is there nothing
else in life you can talk about?

17:31.073 --> 17:33.781
There are other things going
on in the world, you know.

17:33.821 --> 17:35.663
Troubled teens are getting tattoos

17:35.693 --> 17:38.195
in their... underwear area!

17:38.236 --> 17:40.553
I thought I was coming to a hoedown,

17:40.593 --> 17:42.380
but if this is just gonna
be a driver's-license down,

17:42.380 --> 17:44.622
then I guess I will just go somewhere else!

17:51.793 --> 17:52.915
(Hooves clopping)

17:53.595 --> 17:55.096
(Horse whinnies)

18:01.294 --> 18:03.060
- Whoa, Samson.
- (Blusters)

18:03.130 --> 18:04.432
Reverend TimTom.

18:04.552 --> 18:05.793
What you doing, Sue Heck?

18:05.838 --> 18:08.009
I let you down, Reverend TimTom.

18:08.043 --> 18:09.828
I tried to be happy for them,

18:09.843 --> 18:11.630
but I'm still jealous.

18:11.880 --> 18:13.446
Maybe I'm just not meant to drive.

18:13.566 --> 18:15.338
My drive to drive drove my friends away,

18:15.388 --> 18:17.595
so I am done being that driven to drive.

18:17.650 --> 18:20.327
I have decided I am not
gonna get my license.

18:21.823 --> 18:23.150
Let me ask you something.

18:23.455 --> 18:24.851
When you take a test at school,

18:24.891 --> 18:26.118
and you don't have all the answers,

18:26.123 --> 18:28.465
do you just get up and walk away?

18:28.725 --> 18:31.438
No. I would never. I
always answer what I can.

18:31.488 --> 18:33.209
I can still get partial credit.

18:33.329 --> 18:34.246
Exactly.

18:34.656 --> 18:36.308
The Sue Heck I know doesn't quit

18:36.298 --> 18:38.100
after just five tries.

18:38.220 --> 18:39.196
Now hop on.

18:39.875 --> 18:41.423
Where are we going?

18:41.543 --> 18:42.394
You'll see.

18:46.713 --> 18:48.395
- Hyah!
- (Blusters)

18:56.509 --> 18:59.087
(Horse nickers)

18:59.337 --> 19:01.362
(Telephone ringing in distance)

19:01.619 --> 19:03.164
What is this?

19:03.436 --> 19:05.804
What's going on? What are
you guys all doing here?

19:05.924 --> 19:08.241
Reverend TimTom told us you
were feeling jealous of us,

19:08.361 --> 19:09.708
and that's just crazy talk.

19:09.828 --> 19:11.570
<i>Sue, we're jealous of you.</i>

19:11.907 --> 19:13.517
- You are?
- Yeah.

19:13.637 --> 19:14.602
You're smart. You're funny.

19:14.677 --> 19:16.094
You haven't spent any time in juvie.

19:16.139 --> 19:17.881
Nobody in your family has meth teeth.

19:18.181 --> 19:20.417
Not to mention you have
the neck of a queen.

19:20.537 --> 19:21.849
Plus you always try your hardest,

19:21.889 --> 19:24.086
you're always optimistic,
and you never give up.

19:26.379 --> 19:27.845
It's true, Sue.

19:27.900 --> 19:28.686
<i>Mom?</i>

19:28.806 --> 19:30.403
What are you doing here?

19:30.692 --> 19:32.960
Brad called me and told
me it was an emergency...

19:33.080 --> 19:34.682
which it clearly is not,

19:34.802 --> 19:37.055
so thanks for scaring
the crap out of me, Brad.

19:37.235 --> 19:38.672
But the point is,

19:38.932 --> 19:40.582
we believe in you, Sue.

19:40.702 --> 19:42.045
<i>We know you can do this.</i>

19:42.065 --> 19:43.707
I know you can do this.

19:44.032 --> 19:45.338
You're right.

19:45.458 --> 19:47.376
I never give up.

19:47.809 --> 19:49.510
<i>I can do this.</i>

19:49.544 --> 19:50.845
(Keys jangle)

19:50.879 --> 19:52.611
Oh. I am gonna do this right now.

19:52.616 --> 19:53.922
(Cheering)

19:53.943 --> 19:56.120
Sixth time's the charm.

19:56.240 --> 19:57.071
Wait.

19:57.391 --> 19:58.838
This is your sixth time?

19:59.198 --> 20:00.515
Oh, I'm sorry.

20:00.635 --> 20:02.542
You can only take the test five times,

20:02.562 --> 20:04.218
then you have to wait a
month to take it again.

20:04.338 --> 20:06.271
(All groan)

20:07.696 --> 20:10.976
I just have to stay
pumped for four more weeks!

20:11.566 --> 20:12.533
Yeah!

20:12.567 --> 20:15.002
(Cheering)

20:15.036 --> 20:17.062
Aah! (Laughs) Yeah!

20:17.182 --> 20:19.504
<i>There are all kinds of tests in life.</i>

20:19.624 --> 20:21.967
Hi, Axl. Now that we're going out again,

20:22.012 --> 20:23.138
what do you wanna do tonight?

20:23.158 --> 20:25.871
We can sit outside and listen
to the flutter of the bat wings

20:25.891 --> 20:27.708
or, you know, bowling.

20:27.763 --> 20:29.655
(Thudding)

20:29.726 --> 20:31.442
<i>Some you fail over and over,</i>

20:31.472 --> 20:34.059
<i>even if you've been given the answer key.</i>

20:37.713 --> 20:39.145
Yellow pants?

20:39.825 --> 20:41.237
Are you kidding me?

20:41.567 --> 20:43.179
I told you what I wanted.

20:43.354 --> 20:45.301
<i>I told you exactly what I wanted.</i>

20:45.311 --> 20:46.568
I told all of you!

20:46.598 --> 20:48.696
Backmaster 2000!

20:53.190 --> 20:55.763
Well, hey, you haven't
even tried 'em on yet.

21:00.592 --> 21:02.058
Hey!

21:02.178 --> 21:04.542
Oh, yeah. This is so much better.

21:04.587 --> 21:06.283
Who buys someone yellow pants?

21:06.403 --> 21:08.846
Did I say pants? Did I say yellow pants?

21:08.966 --> 21:11.594
Did anybody hear me say "yellow pants"?

21:11.714 --> 21:14.468
I mean, come on. How much
clearer could a person be?

21:14.588 --> 21:16.810
You know what? Next year,
just write me a check.

21:16.930 --> 21:18.601
Hey. They're the ones in charge.

21:18.637 --> 21:20.278
- I just...
- Oh, save it, buddy.

21:20.323 --> 21:22.750
You just wait until
Father's Day. You'll see.

21:23.576 --> 21:26.084
Seriously, what am I
supposed to do with these?

21:31.735 --> 21:33.812
Oh, wow. That's not bad.

